The evidence with the title 'Don't ask, don't tell - Wikipedia ' says The full name of the policy at the time was "don't Ask, DoN't Tell, DoN't Pursue". The " Do N't Ask " provision mandated that military or appointed officials will not ask about or require members to reveal their sexual orientation.The "DoN't Tell" stated that a member may be discharged for claiming to be a homosexual or bisexual  ... 
